    dc:title "A taxonomic revision of South American species of the seed-harvester ant genus Pogonomyrmex (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Part II" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5499126>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5499144>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5499158>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5499146>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5499150>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5499154> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5499126>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Closeup photographs in dorsal view and in profile showing the diversity of mesosomal morphologies for ergatoid queens of Pogonomyrmex: (A–B) P. pencosensis (CASENT0869790), (C–D) P. apterogenos (CASENT0869791), (E–F) P. laticeps (CASENT0217266), (G–H) P. cunicularius (CASENT0173109), and (I–J) P. naegelii (CASENT0869793). Photographs by Robert Johnson and Erin Prado from www.AntWeb.org." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5499126/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5499144>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Closeup photographs for workers of Pogonomyrmex showing dorsum of promesonotum with rugae that are well-defined, very regular and continuous, lacking short lateral branches; longitudinal rugae on mesonotum diverging toward humeral shoulders of pronotum; anterodorsal margin of pronotum with one to several straight, strong, continuous, transverse rugae: (A) P. apterogenos holotype worker (CASENT0914124), (B) P. lagunabravensis holotype worker (CASENT0249051), (C) P. longibarbis (CASENT0249056), and (D) P. sanmartini (CASENT0922481), and dorsum of promesonotum with rugae that are usually wavy to irregular, discontinuous or with short lateral branches; rugae on mesonotum mostly longitudinal but often becoming irregular to rugoreticulate on pronotum; anterodorsal margin of pronotum with wavy to irregular rugae to rugoreticulate, usually with short lateral branches: (E) P. RAJ-altip worker (CASENT0235280), (F) P. andinus (CASENT0914130), (G) P. tafi holotype worker (CASENT0235307), and (H) P. sanmartini (CASENT0922479). Photographs by Michele Esposito from www.AntWeb.org." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5499144/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5499158>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Geographic distribution of: (A) Pogonomyrmex apterogenos, (B) P. araucania, and (C) P. atacama. The large black circle in each panel denotes the type locality." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5499158/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5499146>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Photographs of Pogonomyrmex apterogenos holotype worker: (A) frontal view of head, (B) lateral view of body, and (C) dorsal view of body (CASENT0914124). Photographs by Michele Esposito from www.AntWeb.org." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5499146/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5499150>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Photographs of Pogonomyrmex apterogenos ergatoid queen: (A) frontal view of head, (B) lateral view of body, and (C) dorsal view of body (CASENT0173116). Photographs by April Nobile from www.AntWeb.org." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5499150/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5499154>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Photographs of Pogonomyrmex apterogenos ergatoid male: (A) frontal view of head, (B) lateral view of body, and (C) dorsal view of body (CASENT0173117). Photographs by April Nobile from www.AntWeb.org." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5499154/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

